        </svg>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MANIFESTO -->
    <section id="manifesto" style="border-top:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--bg-2)">
      <div class="om-stack" style={`max-width:${MAXW};margin:0 auto;padding:clamp(64px,8vw,108px) clamp(16px,5vw,28px);display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) 230px;gap:56px`}>
        <div>
          <div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:18px">The principle</div>
          <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:clamp(30px,4vw,46px);line-height:1.08;margin:0 0 28px;color:var(--ink)">Scientific illuminism.</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18.5px;line-height:1.68;color:var(--ink-soft);margin:0 0 20px;text-wrap:pretty"><span style="float:left;font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:78px;line-height:.78;padding:6px 14px 0 0;color:var(--accent)">T</span>he method is older than the word for it: observe, record, repeat, compare. A working is a hypothesis; the journal is the laboratory notebook. Theourgia treats your practice as exactly that — a body of evidence kept with the care a primary source deserves, and queryable like one.</p>
          <p style="font-size:18.5px;line-height:1.68;color:var(--ink-soft);margin:0 0 28px;text-wrap:pretty">Nothing here presumes your cosmology. The tools are tradition-neutral by design; your path surfaces through <em>your</em> content, never through the chrome. Write in plain language or in the tongue the rite demands. The instrument stays quiet so the work can speak.</p>
          <blockquote style="margin:0;padding:18px 0 18px 26px;border-left:2px solid var(--accent);font-family:var(--font-display);font-style:italic;font-size:24px;color:var(--ink)">Solve et coagula.<span style="display:block;margin-top:8px;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-style:normal;font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute)">Dissolve, and bind again.</span></blockquote>
        </div>
        <aside style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--ink-mute);border-top:1px solid var(--line-2);padding-top:14px;align-self:start">
          <p style="margin:0 0 14px"><span style="color:var(--accent)">¹</span> "Scientific illuminism" — the maxim of <span style="font-style:italic">The Equinox</span>: the method of science, the aim of religion.</p>
          <p style="margin:0"><span style="color:var(--accent)">²</span> Every entry is versioned. Saved studies run across the whole record — see <span style="color:var(--ink-soft)">Analytics</span>.</p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TONGUES -->
    <section id="tongues" style="border-top:1px solid var(--line)">
      <div style={`max-width:${MAXW};margin:0 auto;padding:clamp(64px,8vw,108px) clamp(16px,5vw,28px)`}>
        <div class="om-stack" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:48px;align-items:end;margin-bottom:44px">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:18px">One typesystem, many tongues</div>
            <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:clamp(30px,4vw,46px);line-height:1.08;margin:0;color:var(--ink)">Set for every script the work requires.</h2>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:16.5px;line-height:1.62;color:var(--ink-soft);margin:0">Latin, polytonic Greek, and pointed Hebrew share one editorial voice; Arabic, Devanagari, and Coptic are carried by matched companion faces. Every font is a token — swap the whole system per theme.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="om-stack" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-lg);overflow:hidden">
          <div style="background:var(--bg-2);padding:30px 28px"><div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:16px">Latin · Cardo</div><div style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:30px;line-height:1.2;color:var(--ink)">Solve et coagula</div></div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg-2);padding:30px 28px"><div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:16px">Greek (polytonic) · Cardo</div><div lang="el" style="font-family:var(--font-greek);font-size:30px;line-height:1.2;color:var(--ink)">Γνῶθι σαυτόν</div></div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg-2);padding:30px 28px"><div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:16px">Hebrew (niqud) · Frank Ruhl</div><div lang="he" dir="rtl" style="font-family:var(--font-hebrew);font-size:30px;line-height:1.3;color:var(--ink)">בְּרֵאשִׁית בָּרָא</div></div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg-2);padding:30px 28px"><div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:16px">Arabic · Noto Naskh</div><div lang="ar" dir="rtl" style="font-family:var(--font-arabic);font-size:30px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--ink)">بِسْمِ اللّٰه</div></div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg-2);padding:30px 28px"><div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:16px">Devanagari · Noto Serif</div><div lang="sa" style="font-family:var(--font-deva);font-size:30px;line-height:1.4;color:var(--ink)">ॐ तत् सत्</div></div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg-2);padding:30px 28px"><div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:16px">Coptic · Noto Sans</div><div lang="cop" style="font-family:var(--font-coptic);font-size:30px;line-height:1.3;color:var(--ink)">ⲡⲛⲟⲩⲧⲉ</div></div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin:30px 0 0;font-size:20px;line-height:1.75;color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:64ch">Scripts mix cleanly mid-sentence: the theurgist invokes the <span lang="el" style="font-family:var(--font-greek);color:var(--ink)">ἀγαθὸς δαίμων</span> and seals the working with <span lang="he" dir="rtl" style="font-family:var(--font-hebrew);color:var(--ink)">אֱמֶת</span> — direction, baseline, and font selection handled for you.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TOOLKIT -->
    <section id="toolkit" style="border-top:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--bg-2)">
      <div style={`max-width:${MAXW};margin:0 auto;padding:clamp(64px,8vw,108px) clamp(16px,5vw,28px)`}>
        <div style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin-bottom:18px">The toolkit</div>
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:clamp(30px,4vw,46px);line-height:1.08;margin:0 0 8px;color:var(--ink)">Everything the practice needs.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:56ch;margin:0 0 44px">One vault for the record, the rite, and the research. Each surface is colour-coded by content type so the structure reads at a glance.</p>
        <div class="om-stack" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-lg);overflow:hidden">
          {[
            { color: "var(--c-journal)", title: "Journal", body: "Versioned entries, tags, entities, and full-text search across every working.", icon: "M12 6c-2-1.3-4.6-1.5-7-.9v12.4c2.4-.6 5-.4 7 .9 2-1.3 4.6-1.5 7-.9V5.1c-2.4-.6-5-.4-7 .9z M12 6v12.4" },
            { color: "var(--c-divination)", title: "Divination", body: "Tarot, I Ching, geomancy, runes and scrying — each casting timestamped and queryable.", icon: "M2 12s3.6-6.5 10-6.5S22 12 22 12s-3.6 6.5-10 6.5S2 12 2 12z M12 9.4 a2.6 2.6 0 1 0 0 5.2 a2.6 2.6 0 0 0 0-5.2z" },
            { color: "var(--c-working)", title: "Sigil Studio", body: "Compose, charge, and archive sigils. Parameters and gematria travel with the glyph.", icon: "M12 3a9 9 0 1 0 0 18 9 9 0 0 0 0-18z M12 4.5l6.5 11.3H5.5z" },
            { color: "var(--c-entity)", title: "Entity Index", body: "Gods, daimones, angels, saints and ancestors — cross-referenced to every appearance.", icon: "M6 6h12M7 9.5h10M9 9.5v8M15 9.5v8M5 20.5h14" },
            { color: "var(--c-library)", title: "Library", body: "Your grimoires and primary sources, cited inline with page-accurate references.", icon: "M5 4h3v16H5z M10 4h3v16h-3z M16 5l3.4.9-3.2 14.5L13 19" },
            { color: "var(--c-synchronicity)", title: "Calendars & Hours", body: "Planetary hours, lunar phase and transits across multiple calendars, layered on every date.", icon: "M3.5 5.5h17v15h-17zM3.5 10h17M8 3v4M16 3v4" },
